Diplomatic talks over Ukraine between Russia and the West yielded no breakthroughs. Is there still room for compromise to avoid open conflict? The World Bank downgrades the forecast for global economic growth in 2022 to 4.1%. What explains the drop and what are the potential risks ahead? Birth rates during pandemic hit record lows in several countries. How did an expected ‘baby boom’ turn into a ‘baby bust’? For the edition of Dialogue Weekend, we have Pavel Felgenhauer, Russian defense analyst; Harvey Dzodin, senior fellow of the Center for China and Globalization; Prof. John Gong from University of International Business & Economics; and Hong Hao, chief strategist of Bank of Communications (International).